<elementSpec xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" module="core" xml:id="ORIG" usage="opt" ident="orig">
<equiv/>
<gloss>original form</gloss>
<desc>contains  a reading which is marked as following  the original,
rather than being normalized or corrected.</desc>
  <classes>
    <memberOf key="model.pPart.edit"/>
    <memberOf key="model.choicePart"/>
  </classes>
  <content>
    <rng:ref xmlns:rng="http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0" name="macro.phraseSeq"/>
  </content>
  <attList>
  </attList>
  <exemplum>
    <p>If all that is desired is to call attention to the original version in the copy text,
      <gi>orig</gi> may be used alone:</p>
      <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><l>But this
      will be a <orig>meere</orig> confusion</l>
<l>And hardly shall we all be <orig>vnderstoode</orig></l>
</egXML>  </exemplum>
  <exemplum>
    <p>More usually, an <gi>orig</gi> will be combined with a
    regularized form within a <gi>choice</gi> element:</p>
      <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><l>But this
      will be a <choice><orig>meere</orig><reg>mere</reg></choice> confusion</l>
<l>And hardly shall we all be <choice><orig>vnderstoode</orig><reg>understood</reg></choice></l>
      </egXML>
<!--   <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><choice><orig>W</orig><reg resp="jb">Ui</reg></choice>t haeren gouden mondt: als hy eens open gaetb</egXML>
    <note type="cit">From //TEI/web/Applications/Samples/ep02-he1608v1.xml</note -->
<p><note type="cit">Kyd, Spanish Tragedy, (1592) Kv</note> </p>
  </exemplum>
  <remarks/>
  <listRef>
    <ptr target="#COEDREG" type="div2"/>
    <ptr target="#TC" type="div1"/>
  </listRef>
</elementSpec>
